		<!-- ParagraphItems -->
		<p>
<p>WAKEFIELD, Mass. (Feb. 4, 2015) &mdash; Alliance Tire Americas (ATA) is adding eight staff members to its U.S. group as it continues to expand its presence in the U.S. market.</p>
<p>Alliance said Kelly Klofas, Joel Saslaw, Luke Van Epps and David Dzierzek join the group with a focus on sales and customer support across the U.S. They will be based at Alliance&rsquo;s corporate offices in Wakefield.</p><p>Additionally, David Brown, Chan Photoisane, Christopher Light and Ronzell Lavergne join offices located in Texas, California and Alabama and are also focused on sales development and customer support, according to the tire marketer.</p><p>&ldquo;We are very excited to the welcome these new members to the Alliance team,&rdquo; said James Clark, president of Alliance Tire Americas, the Wakefield-based subsidiary of India's Alliance Tire Group (ATG).</p><p>&ldquo;From our headquarters just outside of Boston to our offices across the country, we are building our staff to deliver the exceptional customer service and product support that have become hallmarks of Alliance Tire.&rdquo;</p><p>He added that the company plans on more additions of both customers and staff in 2015 and beyond as sales of the Alliance, Galaxy and Primex brands &mdash; as well as demand for Aeolus truck tires, which ATA distributes in North America &mdash; continue to increase.</p><p></p><p></p>
</p>
	

